    <section>
      <h3>about</h3>
      <p>
        HCI/CSCW researcher; empathetic moderator; contemplative flâneur;
        resource-sharing strategist; lifetime learner (plus EV enthusiast
        and unapologetic YouTube binge-watcher).
      </p>
      <p>
        PhD Candidate at UXLAB, Seoul National University.
        Previously studied Political Science & French Literature (BA),
        French Linguistics (MA), and now Human-Computer Interaction (PhD).
      </p>
      <p>
        Research interests include account sharing, informal coordination,
        psychological ownership, human agency, game theory,
        and human–AI communication.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>papers & proceedings</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>“Don’t Look, But I Know You Do”: Norms and Observer Effects in Shared LLM Accounts — CHI 2026</li>
        <li>“I might be using his... but it is also mine!”: Ownership & Control in Account Designed for Sharing — CHI 2021</li>
        <li>When Multiple Users Meet Multiple Profiles — HCI Korea 2019</li>
        <li>The Ephemerality of Instagram Stories — HCI Korea 2019</li>
        <li>Exploring Knowledge Landscape in User Experiences Using Author Keyword Analysis</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>projects</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>UX Evaluation Criteria for Text-Centered Conversational Experiences — LG Electronics / Advisor</li>
        <li>Co-Living Clothing Care Pilot — Samsung Electronics / Project Manager</li>
        <li>Subscription Service Strategy Research — Samsung Electronics / Advisor</li>
        <li>Bixby: UX Next Step Strategy — Samsung Electronics / Advisor</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>talks & workshops</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Everyday Writings with LLMs — House of Green (2025)</li>
        <li>Zettelkasten & Obsidian Workshop — House of Green (2024)</li>
        <li>Doctoral Colloquium — HCI Korea (2023)</li>
        <li>Outstanding Paper Presentation — HCI Korea (2022)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>contact</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>jieun.song [at] snu.ac.kr</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <footer>
      Last updated 2026.03.03
    </footer>

  </main>
</body>
